metadata.name: Housh - The Goddess of Breath
metadata.description:
Housh is the dream goddess of breath.  She is the subconscious facet of the element of air and is related to the waking worldâ€™s spirits the wind and sky.  Her concern is that of the deep respiration of the sleeper. 

Housh appears in dreams as a mysterious and surreal woman or figure in a white and gold hooded robe often billowing in the breeze.
